  {
    "encid": "mJ-JlpORcZZFfwJ0zrqXjg",
    "text": {
      "full": "Not sure where to start. Best meal I had in Seattle. Spent a full day walking around, seeing the touristy spots and bars. Came here for a late night dinner Thursday night without a reservation but were seated right away. The place was lively with patrons but our table felt cozy. Our server was welcoming and very attentive. The drinks were delicious (forgot exactly what we ordered, but all the cocktails looked great on the menu). The fish & chips hit the spot but it was almost too much food for us as we could not get over the king salmon pasta. Maybe it's because I've never had salmon in my pasta, or maybe I've never experienced sourdough pasta. Whatever it was, this dish is a star and I need to come back to eat this again. I'm salivating just writing this. The location is perfect if you're near the waterfront or Pike Market. Can't wait to return!",
      "language": "en"
    },
